+# Two-Axis Review Evidence
+
+Range: `41df4f51...6d79db01`
+
+## Standards Pass
+
+- High: correction reconciliation accepts a historical resolver after a different current tail.
+- High: 009E replay response and public error codes diverge from source API §§7/45.2.
+- High: mutable source-bank labels are treated as governed truth.
+- Medium: initiation fragments the named workflow owner around private readiness structures.
+- Medium: 009E tests mock every business owner and under-assert zero-artifact denials.
+- Medium: initiation audit evidence omits mandatory request/comment attribution.
+
+## Spec Pass
+
+- High: governed CFO/CFC authority is excluded by primary-only role resolution.
+- High: 009E has no genuine owner-backed public or race acceptance path.
+- Medium: unrelated signature history poisons the five-family readiness decision.
+- Medium: retained initiation action evidence cannot reconcile verification context.
+
+## Reconciliation
